  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nCLI options that accept multiple values will treat any unknown value that follows as just another value, which can cause mistyped CLI options to go unnoticed.\r\n\r\nFor example `teku --foo --eth1-endpoints http://localhost:8545` will correctly fail to start and report that `--foo` is an unknown option.  However `teku --eth1-endpoints http://localhost:8545 --foo` will start and log errors about the second eth1 endpoint not starting with http: or https: (it's treating `--foo` as an eth1 endpoint).\r\n\r\nThis also happens with options like `--metrics-host-allowlist`.  Values that start with `--` should always be considered as a new CLI option rather than another value to avoid this confusion.",
