    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We use PicoCLI (https://picocli.info) for our command line parsing.  `BeaconNodeCommand` is the class to start at which includes most options via `@Mixin` annotations with the actual option definitions being in separate files in `teku/src/main/java/tech/pegasys/teku/cli/options`.\n\nPicoCLI has a useful looking option we should test: `setUnmatchedOptionsAllowedAsOptionParameters` (https://picocli.info/#_option_parameters_resembling_options).  The best place for setting that would be in `BeaconNodeCommand.registerConverters` (which I'd suggest then renaming to something like `configurePicoCli` or `configureCommandLine`. We should also add a test in `BeaconNodeCommandTest` to confirm that the unknown value is rejected (the existing test `unknownOptionShouldDisplayShortHelpMessage` is a good example of checking that an invalid value was detected.",
